        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 6:19PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 618 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pueblo Depot, or 12 miles east of Pueblo Airport, moving east at 20
mph. Thunderstorm winds may extend well ahead of storms.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Olney Springs, Boone, Crowley, and Pueblo Depot.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
